output.crosstab_text:
For first degree graduates of English studies, 1 years after graduation, Education was the most common industry for White and Mixed ethnicity graduates, Administrative and support service activities was the most common industry for Black ethnicity graduates, Wholesale and retail trade - repair of motor vehicles and motorcycles was the most common industry for Asian ethnicity graduates, Accommodation and food service activities, Administrative and support service activities, Education, Human health and social work activities, Information and communication, Not known and Wholesale and retail trade - repair of motor vehicles and motorcycles was the most common industry for Other ethnicity graduates, and Administrative and support service activities, Education and Professional, scientific and technical activities was the most common industry for Not known ethnicity graduates.

The industry with the largest range in proportions was Accommodation and food service activities where Other ethnicity graduates had the highest proportion and Asian ethnicity graduates had the lowest proportion. The industry with the largest range in median earnings was Administrative and support service activities where Mixed ethnicity graduates had the highest median earnings (£19,700) and Asian ethnicity graduates had the lowest median earnings (£12,000). The group with the highest earnings was Black ethnicity graduates who worked in the Information and communication industry (median earnings of £24,500).
output.crosstab_title: Industry of graduate employment for graduates of English studies by ethnicity, one year after graduation, male and female first degree graduates from English HEIs, APs and FECs, 2018/19 tax year.
